<plot>Adrift in a chaotic summer's evening, a seasoned photographer reflects on modernity and time passing. A photograph of two lovers becomes the pretext for a bitter evaluation of how nowadays our relationship with memories is reduced to consumerism. A chance meeting in a crowded lane is the opportunity for the protagonist to try coming to terms with the world, leading to an unexpected ending.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?352557</url></doc>
